            <bug_when>2014-11-07 11:28:42 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>The JSON3 layer is a additional class to get all browsers on the same JSON level. It fixes some issues in older browsers and adds polyfills for browser which do not offer native JSON support.

However, for qx.next this layer is not needed anymore. Since this layer is not thin I would propose to leave it out completely and use the native JSON methods instead.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
